## Routing Rules

- If a task spans multiple domains (e.g., reviewing a DBT model that processes claims data), prefer the more specialized agent. A healthcare data reviewer who knows DBT is more useful than a generic DBT engineer for clinical pipelines.
- If two agents are equally relevant, route to the one whose review criteria are stricter. Review agents take precedence over implementation agents for review tasks.
- Do not route simple, single-file edits to an agent unless the domain expertise is genuinely needed.
- When a review task involves healthcare data, PHI, or clinical logic, always route to @healthcare-data-reviewer rather than the general @code-reviewer.
- During planning, the implementation agent drafts and the review agent critiques. Both should be consulted before the user sees the final plan.
